{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"tea towel, baking paper, refrigerator","id":"r365448","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-D4vXQLl0fTE\/XZaphdyUY_I\/AAAAAAAAhRo\/g0OIlz6lhxgZSzSuC5z8QExIajao63RLgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_166qNhkcXy22Uu_D.png","title":"Pea and Ginger Soup, Lemon Salmon with Broccoli and Potatoes","publishedAt":"2019-03-09T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"80 g olive oil"},{"content":"50 g soy sauce"},{"content":"½ tsp brown sugar"},{"content":"1 lemon, finely grated zest of half and 25 g juice"},{"content":"4 fresh salmon fillets, skinless (150-180 g each)"},{"content":"1 garlic clove"},{"content":"5 - 10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm), to taste (optional)"},{"content":"100 g shallots, halved"},{"content":"100 g leeks, white part only, cut in pieces"},{"content":"100 g celery stalks, cut in pieces"},{"content":"350 g frozen green peas"},{"content":"450 g water"},{"content":"2 tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"250 g potatoes, cut in pieces (1 cm)"},{"content":"400 g broccoli florets"},{"content":"2 pinches ground black pepper"},{"content":"50 - 100 g single cream, to taste"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"44 g","fat":"44 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"30 g","calories":"2984 kJ \/ 713 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place 30 g oil, soy sauce, sugar, lemon zest and lemon juice in mixing bowl then emulsify <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>. Place salmon fillets in a deep dish and pour over marinade from mixing bowl. Refrigerate for 10 minutes and continue with recipe."},{"content":"Place garlic, ginger (if using), shallots, leeks and remaining 50 g oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>7 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, line Varoma tray with baking paper."},{"content":"Add celery and peas to mixing bowl then chop <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add water and 1 tsp salt. Insert simmering basket and weigh in potatoes. Place Varoma dish into position, weigh in broccoli and season with ½ tsp salt. Insert prepared Varoma tray, arrange salmon fillets on the tray, season with ½ tsp salt and pepper then drizzle with marinade. Cover Varoma and cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep warm. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula, set aside on a plate and cover with a tea towel to keep warm."},{"content":"Add cream to mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and blend <b>2 min\/speed 5<b><strong>-10, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>. Serve soup for starter (see tip), then salmon fillets, potatoes and broccoli for the main course."}],"hintsAndTricks":["A quick, healthy meal full of bright flavours and colours, starting with a vibrant green pea soup with zingy ginger, followed by lemon-marinated salmon with steamed potatoes and broccoli. This multi-level recipe can turn a weeknight dinner into a special treat.","If making a carrot soup instead of a pea soup, make sure carrots are cut in small pieces.","If the celery stalks have leaves, place a few leaves on top of salmon fillets before steaming to add extra flavour.","For a milder taste, omit drizzling salmon with marinade in <b>step 4.<b>","After serving the soup, set mixing bowl and covered Varoma back in position so the main course keeps warm while the soup is enjoyed."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","4 portions"]}